    b"onMemorySearchHints\x00\x00\x01\x00J\x0e\x00\x00\x0a        {{ _.role(\"system\") }}\x0a\x0a        Choose memor"
    b"y search hints for the selected task and current request.\x0a\x0a        The hints wil"
    b"l drive memory search before the selected task runs.\x0a\x0a        Stop once the hint"
    b"s look good enough for the request without thinking about it too much.\x0a\x0a        "
    b"Search surfaces:\x0a        - tags: exact memory tags. They are not substring searc"
    b"hed.\x0a        - strings.contains: case-insensitive text fragments. Each value is "
    b"checked\x0a          as a substring against searchable memory content.\x0a        - st"
    b"rings.equals: exact text values. Each value is checked for exact\x0a          equal"
    b"ity against searchable memory content.\x0a\x0a        Optional outputs available in th"
    b"is step:\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation that could b"
    b"e useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Return only search hin"
    b"ts and optional candidate_memory.\x0a        - Search hints are alternatives during"
    b" retrieval; a memory can be useful\x0a          when any positive tag or string hin"
    b"t matches.\x0a        - Prefer tags.any_of for positive tag hints.\x0a        - Leave "
    b"tags.all_of empty unless compatibility with older memories needs it.\x0a        - U"
    b"se tags.none_of only for clear exclusions.\x0a        - Use strings.contains for du"
    b"rable words or phrases that should appear\x0a          inside a relevant memory.\x0a  "
    b"      - Use strings.equals only for exact text that should match a relevant\x0a    "
    b"      memory value as a whole.\x0a        - Prefer a small set of high-signal hints"
    b" over broad keyword stuffing.\x0a        - Return empty arrays when no useful searc"
    b"h hint is available.\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they are useful.\x0a\x0a"
    b"        {{ _.role(\"user\") }}\x0a\x0a        Current user request:\x0a        {{ current_u"
    b"ser_request }}\x0a\x0a        Conversation history:\x0a        {% if current_conversation"
