    b"      You choose one task for the current user request.\x0a\x0a        Use the availab"
    b"le task information and context to decide which task should\x0a        run next.\x0a\x0a "
    b"       Stop once you have the right task without thinking about it too much. Don"
    b"'t waste time thinking about the agent_thought too much.\x0a\x0a        Context sectio"
    b"ns:\x0a        - Current user request: the request being routed now.\x0a        - Conv"
    b"ersation history: earlier human and agent messages.\x0a        - Session memories: "
    b"remembered observations for this session.\x0a        - Available tasks: the only ta"
    b"sks that may be selected.\x0a        - Task-choice memories: remembered observation"
    b"s about choosing tasks.\x0a\x0a        Optional outputs available in this step:\x0a      "
    b"  - agent_thought: private context to add to the conversation without\x0a          "
    b"notifying the human.\x0a        - candidate_memory: a vague remembered observation "
    b"that could be useful to\x0a          preserve.\x0a\x0a        Rules:\x0a        - Select exa"
    b"ctly one task from Available tasks.\x0a        - selected_task_id must exactly matc"
    b"h an available task id.\x0a        - Do not invent task ids.\x0a        - Do not perfo"
    b"rm the task. Only choose the task.\x0a        - Use optional outputs only when they"
    b" are useful.\x0a        - User request may be related to memories that this layer i"
    b"s not yet aware of, simply finish your task without thinking too much if that se"
    b"ems to be the case.\x0a        - Do not generate misleading agent_thoughts that wou"
    b"ld only be relevant to your lack of memory capabilities.\x0a\x0a        {{ _.role(\"use"
    b"r\") }}\x0a\x0a        Current user request:\x0a        {{ current_user_request }}\x0a\x0a      "
    b"  Conversation history:\x0a        {% if current_conversation %}\x0a        Conversati"
